During the years ended December 31, 2018 and December 31, 2016, the Company converted intercompany loans with a
foreign subsidiary to equity, which resulted in losses for tax purposes. The loans had been historically treated as components of the
Company’s investments in that subsidiary, and as a result, foreign currency gains and losses on the loans had been accumulated as a
component of other comprehensive (loss) income. The subsidiary continues to operate as part of the
Company. The tax benefits of $5.0 million and $16.8 million, respectively, which were triggered by the conversion, were therefore
allocated to other comprehensive (loss) income rather than net income (loss).
